{"questionId":"9074553","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>An experiment to investigate simple harmonic motion consists of a mass oscillating at the&nbsp;end of a vertical spring.</p>\n<p><img style=\"display:block;margin-left:auto;margin-right:auto;\" src=\"__IMG__/6636582516f7d38dd44465d0f1905463a4dc9fd9.png\"></p>\n<p>The mass oscillates vertically above a motion sensor that measures the speed of the mass.&nbsp;Test 1 is carried out with a 1.0 kg mass and spring of spring constant <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>k</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></math>. Test 2 is a repeat of&nbsp;the experiment with a 4.0 kg mass and spring of spring constant <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>k</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></math>.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>The variation with time of the vertical speed of the masses, for one cycle of the oscillation,&nbsp;is shown for each test.<br><br></p>\n<p>&nbsp;<img style=\"display:block;margin-left:auto;margin-right:auto;\" src=\"__IMG__/e846b329a70913c043cf5940de814e71bac66342.png\"></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Deduce&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><msub><mi>k</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><msub><mi>k</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></mfrac></math>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>k</mi><mo>∝</mo><mi>m</mi></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>OR&nbsp;</strong></em>&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><msub><mi>m</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><msub><mi>k</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><msub><mi>m</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><msub><mi>k</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></mfrac></math>&nbsp;✓</p>\n<p>0.25&nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>OR&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>4</mn></mfrac></math>&nbsp;</strong></em>✓</p>","meta":{"questionId":"9074553","referenceCode":"22M.2.HL.TZ2.a.ii","subjectId":"46-dp-physics-last-assessment-2024","title":"Deduce k1k2.","paper":"2","level":"HL","questionNumber":"a.ii","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Additional higher level (AHL)","Additional higher level (AHL)","Topic 9: Wave phenomena","9.1 – Simple harmonic motion","Additional higher level (AHL)","Topic 9: Wave phenomena"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}